                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/1556: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-04T16:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 4, 1935—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 4—11:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>493. My 492, October 4, noon. His Majesty’s Government do not consider a state of
                    war exists. They have promised to keep in touch with me on this question.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bingham</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
